<paragraph blockId="6.[144,1104,471,559]" pageId="6" pageNumber="2646">This species differs from the others by the prothorax without tubercles, rounded at the sides; elytra short, about three or four times as long as the prothorax, and colour black with dark-blue reflections.</paragraph>
